00232 /*********************************************************************************************************//**
00233   * @brief  USB Class Report Process for application (Loopback for CONTROL Transfer).
00234   * @retval None
00235   ***********************************************************************************************************/
00236 static void USBDClass_ReportProcess(void)
00237 {
00238   u32 i;
00239 
00240   // Output Report (ID = RPT_ID_3) from the CONTROL Transfer loopback to Input Report (ID = RPT_ID_1)
00241   if (gIsSetOutputReport3 == TRUE)
00242   {
00243     //gRPT_BufferN[0] is Report ID, do not change it
00244     for (i = 1; i <= RPT_LEN_1; i++)
00245     {
00246       gRPT_Buffer1[i] = gRPT_Buffer3[i];
00247     }
00248     gIsSetOutputReport3 = FALSE;
00249   }
00250 
00251   // Output Report (ID = RPT_ID_4) from the CONTROL Transfer loopback to Input Report (ID = RPT_ID_2)
00252   if (gIsSetOutputReport4 == TRUE)
00253   {
00254     //gRPT_BufferN[0] is Report ID, do not change it
00255     for (i = 1; i <= RPT_LEN_2; i++)
00256     {
00257       gRPT_Buffer2[i] = gRPT_Buffer4[i];
00258     }
00259     gIsSetOutputReport4 = FALSE;
00260   }
00261   return;
00262 }
00263 
00264 /*********************************************************************************************************//**
00265   * @brief  USB Class Endpoint 1 IN Process for application (Loopback for INTERRUPT Transfer).
00266   * @retval None
00267   ***********************************************************************************************************/
00268 static void USBDClass_EPT1INProcess(void)
00269 {
00270   u32 i;
00271 
00272   // Output Report (ID = RPT_ID_3) from the INTERRUPT Transfer loopback to Input Report (ID = RPT_ID_1)
00273   if (gIsWriteOutputReport3 == TRUE)
00274   {
00275     if (gIsEP1INEmpty == TRUE)
00276     {
00277       gIsEP1INEmpty = gIsWriteOutputReport3 = FALSE;
00278 
00279       gRPT_Buffer1[0] = RPT_ID_1;
00280       //gRPT_BufferN[0] is Report ID, do not change it
00281       for (i = 1; i <= RPT_LEN_1; i++)
00282       {
00283         gRPT_Buffer1[i] = gRPT_Buffer3[i];
00284       }
00285 
00286       USBDCore_EPTWriteINData(USBD_EPT1, (u32 *)gRPT_Buffer1, RPT_LEN_1 + 1);
00287     }
00288   }
00289 
00290   // Output Report (ID = RPT_ID_4) from the INTERRUPT Transfer loopback to Input Report (ID = RPT_ID_2)
00291   if (gIsWriteOutputReport4 == TRUE)
00292   {
00293     if (gIsEP1INEmpty == TRUE)
00294     {
00295       gIsEP1INEmpty = gIsWriteOutputReport4 = FALSE;
00296     
00297       gRPT_Buffer2[0] = RPT_ID_2;
00298       //gRPT_BufferN[0] is Report ID, do not change it
00299       for (i = 1; i <= RPT_LEN_2; i++)
00300       {
00301         gRPT_Buffer2[i] = gRPT_Buffer4[i];
00302       }
00303 
00304       USBDCore_EPTWriteINData(USBD_EPT1, (u32 *)gRPT_Buffer2, RPT_LEN_2 + 1);
00305     }
00306   }
00307   return;
00308 }

00310 /*********************************************************************************************************//**
00311   * @brief  USB Class Endpoint 2 OUT Process for application (Read Outpur Report from the INTERRUPT Transfer).
00312   * @retval None
00313   ***********************************************************************************************************/
00314 static void USBDClass_EPT2OUTProcess(void)
00315 {
00316   if (gIsEP2OUTReady == TRUE)
00317   {
00318     gEP2Len = USBDCore_EPTReadOUTData(USBD_EPT2, (u32 *)gOutputReportBuffer, 64);
00319 
00320     __DBG_USBPrintf("%06ld EP2OUT\t[%02d]\r\n", ++__DBG_USBCount, (int)gEP2Len);
00321     __DBG_USBDump((uc8 *)gOutputReportBuffer, gEP2Len);
00322 
00323     gIsEP2OUTReady = FALSE;
00324 
00325     switch (gOutputReportBuffer[0])
00326     {
00327       case RPT_ID_3:
00328       {
00329         gIsWriteOutputReport3 = TRUE;
00330         _MEM_Copy(gOutputReportBuffer, gRPT_Buffer3, gEP2Len);
00331         break;
00332       }
00333       case RPT_ID_4:
00334       {
00335         gIsWriteOutputReport4 = TRUE;
00336         _MEM_Copy(gOutputReportBuffer, gRPT_Buffer4, gEP2Len);
00337         break;
00338       }
00339       default:
00340       {
00341         break;
00342       }
00343     }
00344   }
00345 
00346   return;
00347 }

00379 {
00380   u16 uUSBCmd = *((u16 *)(&(pDev->Request)));

00451 /*********************************************************************************************************//**

00454   * @retval None
00455   ***********************************************************************************************************/
00456 static void USBDClass_Standard_GetDescriptor(USBDCore_Device_TypeDef *pDev)
00457 {
00458   u32 type = pDev->Request.wValueH;
00459 
00460   switch (type)
00461   {
00462     case DESC_TYPE_21_HID:
00463     {
00464       pDev->Transfer.pData = (uc8 *)((pDev->Desc.pConfnDesc) + CLASS_DESC_OFFSET);
00465       pDev->Transfer.sByteLength = DESC_LEN_HID;
00466       pDev->Transfer.Action = USB_ACTION_DATAIN;
00467       break;
00468     }
00469     case DESC_TYPE_22_RPOT:
00470     {
00471       pDev->Transfer.pData = (uc8 *)(USB_HID_ReportDesc);
00472       pDev->Transfer.sByteLength = DESC_LEN_RPOT;
00473       pDev->Transfer.Action = USB_ACTION_DATAIN;
00474       break;
00475     }
00476     case DESC_TYPE_23_PHY:
00477     {
00478       break;
00479     }
00480   } /* switch (type)                                                                                        */
00481 
00482   return;
00483 }

00511 /*********************************************************************************************************//**
00512   * @brief  USB Device Class Request - GET_REPORT
00513   * @param  pDev: pointer of USB Device
00514   * @retval None
00515   ***********************************************************************************************************/
00516 static void USBDClass_GetReport(USBDCore_Device_TypeDef *pDev)
00517 {
00518   u32 value = pDev->Request.wValueH;
00519   //u32 len = pDev->Request.wLength;
00520   u32 id = pDev->Request.wValueL;
00521 
00522   switch (value)
00523   {
00524     case HID_RPOT_TYPE_01_INPUT:

00819 /*********************************************************************************************************//**
00820   * @brief  Memory Copy
00821   * @param  Src: Source address pointer
00822   * @param  Dest: Destination address pointer
00823   * @param  len: Length for copy
00824   * @retval None
00825   ***********************************************************************************************************/
00826 static void _MEM_Copy(u8 *Src, u8 *Dest, u32 len)
00827 {
00828   u32 i;
00829   for (i = 0; i < len; i++)
00830   {
00831     *Dest = *Src;
00832     Dest++;
00833     Src++;
00834   }
00835 }
